Target: The Environmental Measurement Station ontology (OntoEMS) is an ontology developed for representing environmental measurement stations, reported quantities, and time series of associated readings.

Comment: A station (physical or virtual) reporting a quantity.
Label: Reporting station

Comment: A reporting station that reports the level of water (potentially besides any other environmental observations).
Label: Water level reporting station

Comment: A prediction or estimation of a quantity.
Label: Forecast

Comment: The height reached by the water in a reservoir, river, the tide at sea, or similar.
Label: Water level

Comment: The height reached by the water in a reservoir, river, the tide at sea, or similar.
Label: Water level

Comment: The depth of rain that accumulated over a measurement time quantity.
Label: Rainfall

Comment: The depth of rain that accumulated over a measurement time quantity.
Label: Rainfall

Comment: The depth of rain that accumulated over a measurement time quantity.
Label: Rainfall

Comment: The volume of water which passes a river cross section per unit time.
Label: Water flow

Comment: Temperature of the outside air that would be indicated by a thermometer exposed to the air at a location sheltered from direct solar radiation.
Label: Air temperature

Comment: Temperature of the outside air that would be indicated by a thermometer exposed to the air at a location sheltered from direct solar radiation.
Label: Air temperature

Comment: Temperature of the outside air that would be indicated by a thermometer exposed to the air at a location sheltered from direct solar radiation.
Label: Air temperature

Comment: Temperature of the outside air as expected to be perceived by a human being, considering the actual air temperature, relative humidity and the strength of the wind at 5 feet as well as an understanding of how heat is lost from the human body during cold and windy days.
Label: Feels-like temperature

Comment: Velocity of outside air movement.
Label: Wind speed

Comment: Velocity of outside air movement.
Label: Wind speed

Comment: Maximum velocity of short-lived peaks in wind speed.
Label: Wind gust

Comment: Maximum velocity of short-lived peaks in wind speed.
Label: Wind gust

Comment: Direction from where the wind is blowing measured relative to true north (not magnetic north).
Label: Wind direction

Comment: Direction from where the wind is blowing measured relative to true north (not magnetic north).
Label: Wind direction

Comment: Temperature at which the air can no longer hold all of its water vapor, and water vapor starts to condense into liquid water.
Label: Dew point

Comment: Temperature at which the air can no longer hold all of its water vapor, and water vapor starts to condense into liquid water.
Label: Dew point

Comment: Temperature at which the air can no longer hold all of its water vapor, and water vapor starts to condense into liquid water.
Label: Dew point

Comment: The pressure exerted by the atmospheric column of air above the point in question (adjusted to mean sea level).
Label: Atmospheric pressure

Comment: The pressure exerted by the atmospheric column of air above the point in question (adjusted to mean sea level).
Label: Atmospheric pressure

Comment: The pressure exerted by the atmospheric column of air above the point in question (adjusted to mean sea level).
Label: Atmospheric pressure

Comment: Relative humidity of the outside air.
Label: Relative humidity

Comment: Relative humidity of the outside air.
Label: Relative humidity

Comment: Relative humidity of the outside air.
Label: Relative humidity

Comment: Prevailing horizontal distance at which an object can be clearly discerned by a certified weather observer, under current weather conditions.
Label: Visibility

Comment: The strength of the sun's ultraviolet (UV) radiation expressed as index as developed by the World Health Organization.
Label: UV index

Comment: The likelihood of occurrence of precipitation.
Label: Precipitation probability

Comment: The likelihood of occurrence of precipitation.
Label: Precipitation probability

Comment: The concentration of a specific air pollutant as amount of material per unit volume of air (e.g. mass concentration).
Label: Air pollutant concentration

Comment: The total solar irradiance received on a horizontal surface. It is the sum of the horizontal components of direct (beam) and diffuse irradiance.
Label: Global horizontal irradiance

Comment: The total solar irradiance received on a horizontal surface. It is the sum of the horizontal components of direct (beam) and diffuse irradiance.
Label: Global horizontal irradiance

Comment: The total solar irradiance received on a horizontal surface. It is the sum of the horizontal components of direct (beam) and diffuse irradiance.
Label: Global horizontal irradiance

Comment: The horizontal component of direct normal solar irradiance (irradiance arriving in a direct line from the sun as measured on a surface held perpendicular to the sun).
Label: Direct horizontal irradiance

Comment: The horizontal component of direct normal solar irradiance (irradiance arriving in a direct line from the sun as measured on a surface held perpendicular to the sun).
Label: Direct horizontal irradiance

Comment: The horizontal component of direct normal solar irradiance (irradiance arriving in a direct line from the sun as measured on a surface held perpendicular to the sun).
Label: Direct horizontal irradiance

Comment: The horizontal component of diffuse solar irradiance (irradiance that is scattered by the atmosphere).
Label: Diffuse horizontal irradiance

Comment: The horizontal component of diffuse solar irradiance (irradiance that is scattered by the atmosphere).
Label: Diffuse horizontal irradiance

Comment: The horizontal component of diffuse solar irradiance (irradiance that is scattered by the atmosphere).
Label: Diffuse horizontal irradiance

Comment: A relation between an individual measure and a measure aggregate (e.g. individual air pollutant concentration and overall air quality index).
Label: measure of

Comment: A relation between an individual measure and a sum of measures.
Label: included in

Comment: A relationship between a reporting entity and the quantity it reports.
Label: reports

Comment: A relationship between a quantity and its forecast.
Label: has forecasted value

Comment: A relationship between a measure and the respective unit of measure.
Label: has unit

Comment: A relationship between a forecast and the respective unit of measure.
Label: has unit

Comment: A relationship between a measure or forecast and the respective time series.
Label: has time series

Comment: A relationship between a forecast and its creation time.
Label: created on

Comment: Description of data source of reporting station (e.g. API URL)
Label: data source

Comment: Description of unique identifier of reporting station
Label: has identifier

Comment: Description of observation elevation (i.e. in metres)
Label: has observation elevation

Comment: Textual description of instance.
Label: label

Comment: The concentration of sulfur dioxide in the ambient air.
Label: Sulfur dioxide concentration

Comment: The concentration of nitrogen oxides in the ambient air.
Label: Nitrogen oxides concentration

Comment: The concentration of particulate matter in the ambient air.
Label: Particulate matter concentration

Comment: The concentration of ozone in the ambient air.
Label: Ozone concentration

Comment: The concentration of nitrogen monoxide in the ambient air.
Label: Nitrogen monoxide concentration

Comment: The concentration of nitrogen dioxide in the ambient air.
Label: Nitrogen dioxide concentration

Comment: The concentration of carbon monoxide in the ambient air.
Label: Carbon monoxide concentration

Comment: The concentration of carbon dioxide in the ambient air.
Label: Carbon dioxide concentration

Comment: The concentration of particulate matter < 10 µm in the ambient air.
Label: PM10 concentration

Comment: The concentration of particulate matter < 2.5 µm in the ambient air.
Label: PM2.5 concentration

Comment: Relationship between a river level reporting station and the associated catchment name
Label: Catchment name

Comment: Relationship between a river level reporting station and the associated river name
Label: River name

Comment: Relationship between a river level reporting station and the associated stage scale
Label: Stage scale

Comment: Relationship between a stage scale and the lower bound of the typical water level range
Label: Typical range low

Comment: Relationship between a stage scale and the upper bound of the typical water level range
Label: Typical range high

Comment: Relationship between a water level reporting station and its next equivalent downstream
Label: has downstream station

Comment: Relationship between a water level measure and a description of the nature of the reported value (i.e. instantaneous)
Label: Value type

Comment: Relationship between a water level measure and the time period (in sec) over which it was observed
Label: Period

Comment: Relationship between a water level measure and the description whether it refers to the up- or downstream reading
Label: Qualifier

Comment: The range of the current water level reading
Label: Range

Comment: The trend of the current water level reading
Label: Trend

Comment: Current water level is within normal range
Label: Normal range

Comment: Current water level is below normal range
Label: Low range

Comment: Current water level is above normal range
Label: High range

Comment: Current water level range cannot be determined
Label: Unavailable range

Comment: Current water level has been (approximately) constant over last 12 hours
Label: Steady (no trend)

Comment: Current water level has been rising over last 12 hours
Label: Rising trend

Comment: Current water level has been falling over last 12 hours
Label: Falling trend

Comment: Current water level trend cannot be determined
Label: Unavailable trend

Comment: Relationship between a water level measure and its current range
Label: has current range

Comment: Relationship between a water level measure and its current trend
Label: has current trend
